sections.snippet:
The definition of colors should be split into two: a color palette, and uses of those colors in functionally named variables. This makes reskinning and adjustments easy.

[This post explains the concept](http://sachagreif.com/sass-color-variables/)

The trick is to come up with good functional names.

A separate `colors.scss` file should be created for this purpose:

```sass
// Palette
$green : #00FF00;

// Functional uses
$link : $green;
```
